==English==

===Etymology===
Adjectival derivation of Latin [[essentia]] 'being, essence'.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-essential.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''essential'''  (''plural:'' [[essentials]])

# a necessary ingredient
# a [[fundamental]] ingredient

===Adjective===
'''essential'''

# being necessary
# being of high importance
# being in the basic form; showing its [[essence]]
#:''Don't mind him being grumpy.  That's the essential Fred.''

